DurableNameFormat.VIN@Core.Description: A Vehicle identification number (VIN)as specified by ISO 3779:2009, Road vehicles – Vehicle identification number (VIN) – Content and structure, and ISO 3780:2009, Road vehicles – World manufacturer identifier (WMI) code.
DurableNameFormat.NAA@Core.Description: A Name Address Authority (NAA) identifier as specified by the T11 Fibre Channel - Framing and Signaling - 3 (FC-FS-3) specification.
DurableNameFormat.iQN@Core.Description: An iSCSI Qualified Name as specified in RFC 3720 and RFC 3721.
DurableNameFormat.FC_WWN@Core.Description: A Fibre Channel World Wide Name as specified in the T11 Fibre Channel Physical and Signaling Interface Specification.
DurableNameFormat.UUID@Core.Description: A Universally Unique Identifier as specified in the Internation Telecom Union's OSI networking and system aspects - Naming, Addressing and Registration Specification.
DurableNameFormat.EUI@Core.Description: An IEEE-defined 64-bit Extended Unique Identifier as specified in the IEEE's Guidelines for 64-bit Global Identifier (EUI-64) Specification.

EntityState.StandbyOffline@Core.Description: This Entity is enabled, but awaiting an external action to activate it.
EntityState.StandbySpare@Core.Description: This Entity is part of a redundancy set and is awaiting a failover or other external action to activate it.
EntityState.Absent@Core.Description: This Entity is not present or not detected.
EntityState.UnavailableOffline@Core.Description: This Entity is present but cannot be used.
EntityState.Deferring@Core.Description: The Entity will not process any commands but will queue new requests.
EntityState.Quiesced@Core.Description: The Entity is enabled but only processes a restricted set of commands.
EntityState.Updating@Core.Description: The Entity is updating and may be unavailable or degraded.

EntityHealth.Warning@Core.Description: A condition exists that requires attention.
EntityHealth.Critical@Core.Description: A critical condition exists that requires immediate attention.

RackOffsetUnits.@Core.Description: Defines a rack unit of measure.
RackOffsetUnits.OpenU@Core.Description: Defines a rack unit as being equal to 48 mm (1.89 in), as defined in the Open Compute Open Rack specification.
RackOffsetUnits.EIA_310@Core.Description: Defines a rack unit as being equal to 1.75 in (44.45 mm), as specified by the EIA-310 standard.

EntityLocationType.Socket@Core.Description: The type of location is a socket.

EntityArea.Right@Core.Description: The right side of the unit.

Email.@Core.Description: An email address as specified by the Extended Mailbox Address Syntax clause of IETF RFC6531.

PostalAddresses.@Core.Description: Available postal addresses for the contact.

City.@Core.Description: City, township, or shi (JP). see the  RFC5139 A3 field.

HouseNumber.@Core.Description: Numeric portion of house number, see the RFC5139 HNO field.

Room.@Core.Description: Name or number of the room, see the RFC5139 ROOM field.

Placement.@Core.Description: A place within the addressed location.
